We cannot. `Transform._transform` already gets passed the non-container elements of the inputs. For the auto augment transforms, we need to apply multiple transforms to the whole input. To illustrate, this PR proposes

```py
for transform in transforms:
    for non_container_element in inputs:
        transform(non_container_element)
```

while your proposal would mean

```py
for non_container_element in inputs:
    for transform in transforms:
        transform(non_container_element)
```

We reserved the option to override the `forward` of a transform for specifically cases like this, when the common structure does not fit the use case.

