I tried `wait_on` and `wait_until_high` and both of them complains about clock not specified. SystemVerilog has a `wait` construct that blocks the current process execution until the signal is high, and that construct does not depends on clock, see LRM: 9.2. Here is a simple example of `wait`:

```SystemVerilog
module top;
logic a;
initial begin
    wait(a);
    $display("a is set @ %d", $time);
end
initial begin
    #10;
    a = 1;
end
endmodule
```

